<title>UK: Eurotunnel down in London after fire.</title>
<headline>Eurotunnel down in London after fire.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-11-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Eurotunnel units fell 3-1/2 pence to 88 pence on Tuesday following news of a fire in the undersea Channel Tunnel link between France and Britain, the first serious such incident since the tunnel opened.</p>
<p>Two people were seriously injured by toxic smoke and some 34 were evacuated when fire broke out on a shuttle train carrying trucks through the tunnel, closing it to all services.</p>
<p>Shares in ferry operator P&amp;O edged three pence higher to 600-1/2.  </p>
<p>Eurostar said it hoped to resume the express passenger train service from London to Paris by midday on Tuesday but in the meantime passengers would cross the Channel by ferry and coach.</p>
